    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 mandates a single quasi-static load condition and that all three independent modeling teams produced consistent predictions within acceptance bounds. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and has not been applied to this package.",
